          <h2>Overview</h2>
          <p>Remember, remember the fifth of November!</p>
          <p>Get ready for an unforgettable night of fun and fireworks as Plymouth Hoe comes alive on Wednesday 5 November for Bonfire Night!</p>
          <p>Make your way to the iconic Smeaton’s Tower lighthouse for the best views of the bonfire, which will be lit at 7pm. Feel the warmth of the roaring flames as you gather around with friends and family.</p>
          <p>Then, at 7.30pm, prepare to be wowed! The skies will explode with a stunning fireworks display launched from the historic Royal Citadel. Expect an incredible show of rockets, fountains, and crackling firecrackers lighting up the night.</p>
          <p>But the fun doesn’t start there! From 4pm, Plymouth Hoe will be transformed into a buzzing hub of entertainment. With thrilling rides for all ages and a special children's fairground, there's something for everyone. Plus, don’t miss out on the food and drink stalls opening from 5pm to keep you fuelled throughout the night.</p>
          <p>
            It’s the perfect event for the whole family, so wrap up warm, soak in the excitement, and enjoy an evening to remember!
            <br />
          </p>
